{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-corinthians.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:1",
      "text": "Brothers, I couldn’t speak to you as to spiritual, but as to fleshly, as to babies in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:2",
      "text": "I fed you with milk, not with solid food, for you weren’t yet ready. Indeed, you aren’t ready even now,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:3",
      "text": "for you are still fleshly. For insofar as there is jealousy, strife, and factions among you, aren’t you fleshly, and don’t you walk in the ways of men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:4",
      "text": "For when one says, “ I follow Paul,” and another, “ I follow Apollos,” aren’t you fleshly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:5",
      "text": "Who then is Apollos, and who is Paul, but servants through whom you believed, and each as the Lord gave to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:6",
      "text": "I planted. Apollos watered. But God gave the increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:7",
      "text": "So then neither he who plants is anything, nor he who waters, but God who gives the increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:8",
      "text": "Now he who plants and he who waters are the same, but each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:9",
      "text": "For we are God ’s fellow workers. You are God ’s farming, God ’s building.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:10",
      "text": "According to the grace of God which was given to me, as a wise master builder I laid a foundation, and another builds on it. But let each man be careful how he builds on it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:11",
      "text": "For no one can lay any other foundation than that which has been laid, which is Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:12",
      "text": "But if anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, or straw,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:13",
      "text": "each man ’s work will be revealed. For the Day will declare it, because it is revealed in fire; and the fire itself will test what sort of work each man ’s work is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:14",
      "text": "If any man ’s work remains which he built on it, he will receive a reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:15",
      "text": "If any man ’s work is burned, he will suffer loss, but he himself will be saved, but as through fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:16",
      "text": "Don’ t you know that you are God ’s temple and that God ’s Spirit lives in you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:17",
      "text": "If anyone destroys God ’s temple, God will destroy him; for God ’s temple is holy, which you are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:18",
      "text": "Let no one deceive himself. If anyone thinks that he is wise among you in this world, let him become a fool that he may become wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:19",
      "text": "For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, “ He has taken the wise in their craftiness.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:20",
      "text": "And again, “ The Lord knows the reasoning of the wise, that it is worthless.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:21",
      "text": "Therefore let no one boast in men. For all things are yours,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:22",
      "text": "whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come. All are yours,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.3.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:23",
      "text": "and you are Christ ’s, and Christ is God ’s.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
